### Route types and page props

Use the global `Route` namespace types declared in [app/types.ts](mdc:app/types.ts):

- `Route.Context` – passed to `loader`/`action`/`meta`.
- `Route.Loader<T>` / `Route.Action<T>` – handler signatures.
- `Route.PageProps<LoaderFn, ActionFn, Params>` – props passed to `Layout`, `Page`, and route components.

Typing examples:

```tsx
export const loader = (ctx: Route.Context) => ({ message: 'hi' })

export default function Page(props: Route.PageProps<typeof loader>) {
  return <p class="sub">{props.loaderData.message}</p>
}
```

Route meta example (keys consumed by the root layout):

```ts
export const meta: Route.Meta = () => ({
  title: 'Page Title',
  description: 'Optional description',
})
```
